  "text": "2 ) are both macroscopic and different by a factor of 3, so the two states are macroscopically distinguishable. At the same time, the displaced state (2) exhibits robustness to optical losses at the same level as the state (1) before displacement [CITATION_1] . This feature makes this state attractive for studying macro-macro entanglement.",
